description:
A Power Marketer is negotiating a Power Purchase Agreement (PPA) for a 50 MW utility-scale solar project in Phoenix, AZ. The off-taker requires a standard '12x24 profile' — a matrix showing the average hourly AC generation for each hour of the day across each month. Using the Phoenix TMY weather data (path found in /home/ga/.SAM/solar_resource_dir.txt), simulate a 50,000 kW DC system with 1-axis tracking (array type 2), a DC-to-AC ratio of 1.2, inverter efficiency of 96%, and 14% system losses using PySAM.Pvwattsv8. Generate a 12x24 matrix of average hourly AC generation by month and save the results to /home/ga/Documents/SAM_Projects/12x24_profile.json. 

The JSON must follow this structure:
{
  "project_size_kw": 50000,
  "location": "Phoenix, AZ",
  "annual_energy_kwh": <float>,
  "matrix_12x24": {
    "1": [hour0_avg, hour1_avg, ..., hour23_avg],
    "2": [...],
    ...
    "12": [...]
  }
}
